author: AccessWDUN staff
title: Rabun County gets third straight shutout in rout of Social Circle
text:
By AccessWDUN staff Related Articles 2015 High school football rankings 2015 High School Football region standings WEEK 6: Playoff, region races shaping up after big night VIDEO: Gainesville makes most of six Salem turnovers to set up Lanier showdown 
TIGER — Bailey Fisher threw for two touchdowns and Cal Drummond ran for two scores to lead Rabun County to a 44-0 demolition of Social Circle Friday night in Region 8-AA action. 
It was also the third straight shutout for the Wildcats (5-1, 2-0 Region 8-AA) who will travel to Oglethorpe County next week. 
Rabun County needed just one play to get things going. Eli Gipson raced 66 yards on the first play from scrimmage for a quick 7-0 lead just 24 seconds into the game. 
After a punt on their next possession, the Wildcats again needed just one play with Charlie Woerner adding a 32-yard scoring run for a 14-0 lead. Drummond capped their fourth drive of the quarter with a 27-yard touchdown run for a 21-0 lead heading into the second quarter. 
Drummond added his second touchdown of the game four minutes later on a 5-yard run to make it 28-0. Fisher connected with Jack Johnson with 3:44 left in the half on a 60-yard touchdown pass for a 34-0 halftime lead. 
Fisher opened the third quarter with a 42-yard touchdown pass to Alden Wright to push the lead to 41-0 and Kodie Phillips drilled a 25-yard field goal midway through the fourth quarter to cap the scoring. 
Rabun County piled up 503 yards of total offense, including 312 on the ground. Associated Categories : Sports , High School Sports , Friday Game Night Associated Tags : High school football, Rabun County football © Copyright 2015 AccessWDUN.com
